Create a GitHub issue for **{{repoName}}** (`{{repo}}`).

## Steps

1. Ask the user for:
   - **Title** — short and descriptive (no emoji yet)
   - **Type label** — one of: {{#each labels.types}}`{{this}}`{{#unless @last}}, {{/unless}}{{/each}}
   - **Area label** — one of: {{#each labels.areas}}`{{this}}`{{#unless @last}}, {{/unless}}{{/each}}
   - **Priority** — one of: {{#each labels.priorities}}`{{this}}`{{#unless @last}}, {{/unless}}{{/each}} (or skip)
   - **Body** — explore the codebase for relevant file paths and line numbers

2. Prepend the emoji to the title:
{{#each emojiEntries}}
   - `{{label}}` → {{emoji}}
{{/each}}

3. Run:
```bash
gh issue create \
  --repo {{repo}} \
  --title "<emoji + title>" \
  --body "<body>" \
  --label "<type>" \
  --label "<area>"
```

4. Share the issue URL.
